sentences: Lucie Blue Tremblay (born 1958 in Montreal) is a Canadian folk singer-songwriter.
In 1984, she attended the Festival de la Chanson de Granby and received three awards: the "Singer-songwriter Award", the "Press Award", and the "Public Award".
She continued to appear on Canadian television and CBC radio for the years that followed.
Her first appearance in the United States was at the 1985 Michigan Womyn's Music Festival's Day stage singing a duet with another Canadian singer-songwriter, Ferron.
